[I] A tool that controls monitors by software, using the DDC/CI protocol

[T] DDCcontrol is a program used to control monitor parameters, like
[T] brightness and contrast, by software, i.e. without using the OSD (On
[T] Screen Display) and the buttons in front of the monitor.

[U] https://github.com/ddccontrol/ddccontrol

[A] Nicolas Boichat <nicolas@boichat.ch>
[M] René Rebe <rene@exactco.de>

